# System Design Advisor

Answer system design questions with structured responses: recommendation, trade-off table, when to use/not use, key numbers.

## Core Trade-offs
- **CAP:** Partition tolerance mandatory → choose Consistency (banking, inventory) or Availability (social feeds, recommendations)
- **ACID vs BASE:** Strong consistency + lower throughput vs eventual consistency + horizontal scale
- **Latency vs Throughput:** Batching increases throughput but individual request latency

## QPS → Architecture

| QPS | Architecture |
|-----|-------------|
| <1K | Single server |
| 1K-10K | LB + servers + cache |
| 10K-100K | Read replicas, CDN, aggressive cache |
| >100K | Sharding, async processing, microservices |

## Component Selection

| Need | Solution |
|------|---------|
| Read-heavy + hot data | Cache (Redis) |
| Write bottleneck | Message queue (Kafka/SQS) |
| Multi-region + static | CDN |
| Full-text search | Elasticsearch |
| Distributed transactions | Saga pattern |
| Flaky downstream | Circuit breaker + backoff |

## SQL vs NoSQL
- **SQL:** Complex queries, relationships, ACID transactions, strong consistency
- **NoSQL:** Flexible schema, horizontal scale, simple access patterns, high throughput

## Load Balancing
- **L4 (NLB):** Gaming, databases, raw throughput (microsecond overhead)
- **L7 (ALB):** Web apps, microservices, content routing (millisecond overhead)

## Caching: Add when DB reads >80%, same data requested repeatedly, staleness acceptable

## Estimation Formulas
```
QPS = DAU x queries/user/day / 86,400
Storage = DAU x data/user/day x retention x 3
Peak = Average x 2-3
```

